tion.", "availability": "Ayurvedic suppliers; commercial substitute for European V. officinalis in India"}, {"name": "3. Valeriana hardwickii", "slug": "3-valeriana-hardwickii", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 2, "origin": "Eastern Himalayas (Arunachal Pradesh, Mizoram); high altitude species", "traits": "Perennial herb to 150cm; short rhizomes with slender roots; pinnately divided leaves", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "UNSUITABLE for tropical monsoon climates lowlands - requires high elevation cool mountain habitat (similar to V. jatamansi). Recently recorded in Phawngpui National Park. Endangered from habitat loss.", "availability": "Very limited; conservation programs in Northeast India"}, {"name": "4. Valeriana hardwickii var. arnottiana", "slug": "4-valeriana-hardwickii-var-arnottiana", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 3, "origin": "Northwestern Himalayas (Uttarakhand, Milam region)", "traits": "Regional variety of V. hardwickii; similar growth habit but distinct chemical profile", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "UNSUITABLE for tropical monsoon climates. High altitude adaptation only.", "availability": "Research collections only"}, {"name": "5. Red Valerian (Centranthus ruber) - Standard", "slug": "5-red-valerian-centranthus-ruber-standard", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 4, "origin": "Mediterranean", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "MODERATE for tropical monsoon climates. Mediterranean species better adapted to heat than European V. officinalis but still prefers drier conditions than tropical monsoon climates monsoon. May succeed in drier winter season (Dec-Feb). Ornamental only, not medicinal. Listed as invasive in South Africa due to aggressive self-seeding.", "availability": "International seed suppliers; not traditional to India"}, {"name": "6. European Valerian (Valeriana officinalis) - NOT RECOMMENDED", "slug": "6-european-valerian-valeriana-officinalis-not-recommended", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 5, "origin": "Europe, temperate Asia", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "UNSUITABLE for tropical monsoon climates. Requires cool temperate climate with distinct seasons. Tropical monsoon year-round heat and extreme monsoon humidity will cause plant failure. The species naturally prefers zones 4-9 with cool-weather growing seasons. Heat stress, fungal diseases, and poor root development expected. Use Indian Himalayan species instead.", "availability": "N/A - not recommended for cultivation"}], "variety_count": 16}'::jsonb,
